fields.value: Harris 1990 Cross-National Health Care Survey, study no. 902056

dsDescriptionValue.value:
This survey focuses on health care in the U.S., Canada, Japan, Great Britain, Germany, and Sweden. Variables include importance of health care, who is currently receiving health care, quality of care, elective surgery, time waiting to see doctor, cost of health care, satisfaction with current health care, and money spent on physicians, hospitalization, advance medical technology, and terminally ill patients.

United States, Canada, Japan, Great Britain, Germany, and Sweden
